# Local Network & Web Application Penetration Testing Lab

## Project Overview
This project demonstrates basic penetration testing skills using a controlled lab environment.
The goal is to identify vulnerabilities in a local network and a vulnerable web application.

## Tools Used
- Nmap
- Metasploit Framework
- Burp Suite
- Wireshark
- VirtualBox
- Kali Linux
- DVWA / OWASP Juice Shop

## Lab Setup
- Kali Linux (Attacker Machine)
- Vulnerable VM (Metasploitable / DVWA)
- Host-only Network

## Testing Performed
1. Network Scanning using Nmap
2. Vulnerability Identification
3. Safe Exploitation using Metasploit
4. Web Application Testing using Burp Suite
5. Network Traffic Analysis using Wireshark
6. Reporting and Risk Analysis
